2
00:01:04.498 --> 00:01:06.233
Pull over the van!

3
00:01:09.571 --> 00:01:10.672
I'm sorry.

4
00:01:10.705 --> 00:01:11.673
Okay. guys.

5
00:01:12.507 --> 00:01:15.275
I understand what
you're feeling.

6
00:01:15.643 --> 00:01:18.445
We don't need to go
where we're going. okay?

7
00:01:18.478 --> 00:01:21.181
Just pull the van
over and we'll talk.

8
00:01:21.214 --> 00:01:23.150
<i>It feels so good right now.</i>

9
00:01:37.431 --> 00:01:39.132
I just need you to listen. okay?

10
00:01:39.166 --> 00:01:41.636
I just need you to fucking
listen to me! I...!

11
00:01:43.871 --> 00:01:45.205
I'm so sorry.

12
00:01:56.283 --> 00:01:57.885
I don't want to go see the boy!

13
00:01:57.919 --> 00:01:59.621
I don't want to see
the fucking boy!

14
00:01:59.654 --> 00:02:01.522
I don't want to see the boy!

15
00:02:01.556 --> 00:02:03.758
Not the boy!
Not the boy!

16
00:02:03.791 --> 00:02:05.225
Not the boy!

17
00:02:05.258 --> 00:02:06.293
Not the boy!

18
00:02:06.326 --> 00:02:07.160
Not the--

19
00:02:22.610 --> 00:02:25.312
<i>My name is Ellen Hershbergen</i>

20
00:02:25.345 --> 00:02:27.515
<i>and I will tell you</i>
<i>all that happened</i>

21
00:02:27.548 --> 00:02:29.651
<i>in hopes that</i>
<i>it will never happen again.</i>

22
00:02:31.753 --> 00:02:33.955
<i>My mother died in February.</i>

23
00:02:33.988 --> 00:02:35.857
<i>She had been</i>
<i>battling Alzheimer's.</i>

24
00:02:37.892 --> 00:02:40.561
<i>I had been all kinds</i>
<i>of things before that.</i>

25
00:02:41.562 --> 00:02:44.331
<i>A modestly successful</i>
<i>fashion designer.</i>

26
00:02:44.364 --> 00:02:47.401
<i>The author of</i>
<i>a children's book about peas.</i>

27
00:02:48.235 --> 00:02:50.170
<i>Then I became a caretaker.</i>

28
00:02:50.838 --> 00:02:53.675
<i>Now. I wasn't even that.</i>

29
00:02:56.678 --> 00:03:01.949
<i>So all I could do is reinvent</i>
<i>myself and start over.</i>

30
00:03:01.983 --> 00:03:02.950
Morning.

31
00:03:04.018 --> 00:03:04.986
I'm father John Dore.

32
00:03:05.953 --> 00:03:08.221
-Nice to meet you.
-Lovely to meet you. too.

33
00:03:08.823 --> 00:03:10.323
Your call was a godsend.

34
00:03:10.357 --> 00:03:11.793
I've been needing a hand.

35
00:03:11.826 --> 00:03:13.728
but I don't have
the budget to hire

36
00:03:13.761 --> 00:03:14.729
someone full time.

37
00:03:14.762 --> 00:03:17.364
I used to volunteer at
my church in Buffalo.

38
00:03:17.397 --> 00:03:19.667
so I thought it might help me
find my footing here.

39
00:03:19.701 --> 00:03:22.335
And why Pontiac?
How did we get so lucky?

40
00:03:22.369 --> 00:03:24.539
Uh. more chance than luck.

41
00:03:24.939 --> 00:03:26.841
I had this weird feeling

42
00:03:27.675 --> 00:03:30.343
I could fit here.
be myself again.

43
00:03:32.747 --> 00:03:36.349
You know. we could pull
together a yard sale.

44
00:03:36.383 --> 00:03:38.553
raise some money.
fix the pews.

45
00:03:38.586 --> 00:03:39.954
I'm actually pretty good
at that.

46
00:03:40.621 --> 00:03:41.723
Yes.

47
00:03:42.824 --> 00:03:43.925
All right.
It's worth a shot.

48
00:03:43.958 --> 00:03:44.926
Yes.

49
00:03:53.634 --> 00:03:55.503
Donna. Hi.

50
00:03:55.536 --> 00:03:58.740
<i>Ellen. how's the new town</i>
<i>treating you?</i>

51
00:03:58.773 --> 00:04:00.440
Oh. uh.

52
00:04:00.474 --> 00:04:01.374
It's good.

53
00:04:01.408 --> 00:04:04.879
Quiet. Not tripping
over boxes anymore.

54
00:04:04.912 --> 00:04:05.847
It suits me.

55
00:04:05.880 --> 00:04:08.950
<i>I'm glad.</i>
<i>Buffalo will miss you.</i>

56
00:04:08.983 --> 00:04:10.651
<i>You needed a new start.</i>

57
00:04:10.685 --> 00:04:13.654
Yeah. Thanks. Donna.
I really did.

58
00:04:13.688 --> 00:04:16.524
<i>Hey. do you remember</i>
<i>our Cousin Winthrop?</i>

59
00:04:16.557 --> 00:04:17.992
Babysat for him every Thursday.

60
00:04:18.025 --> 00:04:19.459
Ate his weight in spaghetti.

61
00:04:19.493 --> 00:04:20.528
Of course
I remember him.

62
00:04:20.561 --> 00:04:22.663
<i>He's been staying</i>
<i>with us for a while</i>

63
00:04:22.697 --> 00:04:25.298
<i>but Dan wants him gone.</i>

64
00:04:25.332 --> 00:04:26.734
<i>Not enough space</i>
<i>in the house.</i>

65
00:04:26.768 --> 00:04:28.002
Right.

66
00:04:28.035 --> 00:04:30.538
<i>Good news is he's got</i>
<i>a job at a sheet metal plant</i>

67
00:04:30.571 --> 00:04:32.507
<i>not too far</i>
<i>from Pontiac. actually.</i>

68
00:04:32.540 --> 00:04:34.075
<i>Starts in the spring--</i>

69
00:04:34.108 --> 00:04:37.678
You don't even have to finish.
I would be happy to have him.

70
00:04:37.712 --> 00:04:40.648
<i>Really? That would be amazing.</i>

71
00:04:40.681 --> 00:04:41.816
Of course.

72
00:04:41.849 --> 00:04:43.450
<i>He's been bouncing</i>
<i>around family for years.</i>

73
00:04:43.483 --> 00:04:46.353
<i>Like a ball with no air in it.</i>

74
00:04:46.386 --> 00:04:49.690
<i>Just know Winthrop</i>
<i>is a little different.</i>

75
00:04:49.724 --> 00:04:51.526
<i>He has some PTSD stuff</i>

76
00:04:51.559 --> 00:04:53.694
<i>from his time in the army.</i>

77
00:04:53.728 --> 00:04:55.395
<i>But he's a good guy.</i>

78
00:04:56.097 --> 00:04:58.800
All right.
well. we'll figure it out.

79
00:04:58.833 --> 00:05:01.468
I think it might do me some
good to have someone around.

80
00:05:02.435 --> 00:05:04.906
<i>Thank you. Ellen.</i>
<i>Okay. bye.</i>

81
00:05:04.939 --> 00:05:06.908
All right. Bye. Donna.

82
00:05:35.570 --> 00:05:36.571
Winthrop?

83
00:05:40.041 --> 00:05:41.374
Cousin Helen?

84
00:05:42.844 --> 00:05:44.545
It's been a long time.

85
00:05:44.579 --> 00:05:46.379
Only about 30 years.

86
00:05:50.952 --> 00:05:52.086
Is that all you have?

87
00:05:52.854 --> 00:05:53.921
That's all I need.

88
00:05:55.823 --> 00:05:56.958
All right.

89
00:05:57.992 --> 00:06:00.127
I appreciate you taking me in
for a while.

90
00:06:03.197 --> 00:06:04.765
Thank you.

91
00:06:04.799 --> 00:06:05.900
Glad for the company.

92
00:06:06.734 --> 00:06:08.102
It's really good to see you.

93
00:06:20.848 --> 00:06:21.849
This is it.

94
00:06:23.851 --> 00:06:25.385
Let me show you your room.

95
00:06:39.533 --> 00:06:40.534
You like it?

96
00:06:43.170 --> 00:06:44.805
Look. That's us.

97
00:06:55.116 --> 00:06:56.083
Thank you.

98
00:07:02.657 --> 00:07:03.658
Okay.

99
00:07:04.125 --> 00:07:06.861
I had never seen
anyone inhale

100
00:07:06.894 --> 00:07:08.529
spaghetti and meatballs
like you did.

101
00:07:09.063 --> 00:07:10.497
You remember?

102
00:07:10.531 --> 00:07:11.532
It was almost scary.

103
00:07:12.133 --> 00:07:13.167
I still do.

104
00:07:14.669 --> 00:07:16.971
I was sorry to hear
about your mom.

105
00:07:17.004 --> 00:07:17.905
Mm.

106
00:07:19.674 --> 00:07:20.841
Thanks.

107
00:07:21.142 --> 00:07:24.879
I remember her always
laughing. telling jokes.

108
00:07:27.682 --> 00:07:28.683
Mm.

109
00:07:29.250 --> 00:07:31.686
She was a good cook.
like you.

110
00:07:31.719 --> 00:07:33.020
Mm. Thanks.

111
00:07:33.788 --> 00:07:35.022
She was.

112
00:07:35.556 --> 00:07:37.959
She had a laugh that
could fill the whole house.

113
00:07:41.028 --> 00:07:44.497
Then your parents...
nothing about that was fair.

114
00:07:54.041 --> 00:07:55.176
Let's get you some more.

115
00:08:15.730 --> 00:08:17.598
Would it be okay
if I take a bath?

116
00:08:18.232 --> 00:08:19.767
Mm. Of course.

117
00:08:38.219 --> 00:08:39.587
Oh!

118
00:09:41.048 --> 00:09:42.016
Winthrop?

119
00:10:21.822 --> 00:10:23.090
Winthrop?

120
00:10:50.050 --> 00:10:51.185
Hm.

121
00:10:53.287 --> 00:10:55.422
I don't believe I ever met
your uncle Ray.

122
00:10:55.456 --> 00:10:57.158
Your father's
younger brother. right?

123
00:11:02.930 --> 00:11:05.199
I'm sorry.
I don't want to talk about that.

124
00:11:06.934 --> 00:11:07.902
Sure.

125
00:11:13.174 --> 00:11:17.912
I find it hard to reckon what
people do to one another.

126
00:11:20.214 --> 00:11:23.150
No. you don't have to think
about any of that here.

127
00:11:33.127 --> 00:11:35.062
Something's on your mind.

128
00:11:35.796 --> 00:11:37.031
Wanna share?

129
00:11:38.165 --> 00:11:40.467
It's my cousin... Winthrop.

130
00:11:41.168 --> 00:11:42.736
He's staying with me. and...

131
00:11:44.438 --> 00:11:48.809
I'm not sorry I took him in.
but he's been through a lot.

132
00:11:49.410 --> 00:11:51.045
Fought in Afghanistan.

133
00:11:51.345 --> 00:11:52.446
He doesn't sleep.

134
00:11:52.479 --> 00:11:53.781
Walks all night.

135
00:11:55.115 --> 00:11:57.718
Locks himself in the bathroom
for hours.

136
00:11:58.185 --> 00:11:59.987
Eye contact is a struggle.

137
00:12:01.255 --> 00:12:03.791
And I just keep wondering if
he should be with someone

138
00:12:03.824 --> 00:12:07.027
who can handle real PTSD.

139
00:12:07.895 --> 00:12:11.832
Someone who doesn't just sit
outside the bathroom door

140
00:12:11.865 --> 00:12:13.100
hoping he'll come out.

141
00:12:14.368 --> 00:12:16.504
Sometimes that's enough.

142
00:12:16.538 --> 00:12:18.405
Someone waiting
outside the door.

143
00:12:18.973 --> 00:12:20.040
Huh?

144
00:12:21.075 --> 00:12:23.344
That's what
I told myself with my mom.

145
00:12:24.878 --> 00:12:27.214
I stayed in case...

146
00:12:29.883 --> 00:12:33.053
she came back out
just for a minute.

147
00:12:33.087 --> 00:12:34.321
She never did.

148
00:12:35.456 --> 00:12:37.891
I can't let
that happen to Winthrop.

149
00:12:38.292 --> 00:12:41.262
I failed him once.
and I won't do it again.

150
00:12:42.096 --> 00:12:43.297
Ellen...

151
00:12:43.998 --> 00:12:47.067
you did more for her than
most people ever get.

152
00:12:48.002 --> 00:12:49.937
Now you're doing the same
for Winthrop.

153
00:13:14.328 --> 00:13:15.329
Oh.

154
00:13:15.929 --> 00:13:17.798
I'm sorry. I didn't hear
you pull up.

155
00:13:18.566 --> 00:13:19.833
Vahna.

156
00:13:19.867 --> 00:13:21.268
Oh. hi.
I am... I am Ellen.

157
00:13:21.302 --> 00:13:23.103
Oh. wow.

158
00:13:23.137 --> 00:13:26.273
You had a lot of work done here
in such a short amount of time.

159
00:13:26.307 --> 00:13:28.142
Well. it's good to have someone
helping you.

160
00:13:28.175 --> 00:13:29.076
It rains a lot here.

161
00:13:29.109 --> 00:13:32.479
so everything just gets
really overgrown.

162
00:13:32.514 --> 00:13:35.382
I've been living here
for about a year now

163
00:13:35.416 --> 00:13:39.086
and I will
warn you. it is quiet.

164
00:13:39.119 --> 00:13:43.023
There's really like
nothing to do at all.

165
00:13:43.057 --> 00:13:44.091
The closest bar

166
00:13:44.124 --> 00:13:46.260
that doesn't have
a bowling alley attached to it

167
00:13:46.293 --> 00:13:48.162
is actually all the way up
in Buffalo.

168
00:13:48.195 --> 00:13:53.601
Um. I don't drive
or bowl. but it's all good.

169
00:13:53.635 --> 00:13:55.402
Mhm. Mhm.
Want one?

170
00:13:55.436 --> 00:13:56.604
-Oh. no. Thanks.
-I have more

171
00:13:56.638 --> 00:13:58.939
I'm good. I know. thank you.
They look delicious though.

172
00:13:58.972 --> 00:14:00.007
-Yeah.
-Crispy.

173
00:14:00.040 --> 00:14:03.944
I've been having migraines
sort of general all over

174
00:14:03.977 --> 00:14:08.248
aches and pains like every
joint is on fire.

175
00:14:09.450 --> 00:14:11.653
But they got
a pill for that.

176
00:14:11.686 --> 00:14:13.454
They got a pill for everything.
A pill for this.

177
00:14:13.487 --> 00:14:15.456
a pill for that.
Pill for the fucking pills.

178
00:14:17.091 --> 00:14:19.126
I actually moved here

179
00:14:19.159 --> 00:14:22.096
because I was going to take
some college classes.

180
00:14:22.129 --> 00:14:23.665
You know. Genesee College.
-Yeah. yeah.

181
00:14:23.698 --> 00:14:24.898
- Just up.
- Yeah.

182
00:14:24.932 --> 00:14:25.966
Poetry.

183
00:14:25.999 --> 00:14:27.167
Oh.

184
00:14:27.201 --> 00:14:30.270
I did get involved
with the... teacher.

185
00:14:31.438 --> 00:14:32.873
Grace. whose...

186
00:14:34.274 --> 00:14:38.212
a bitch and dumped me
out of a blue.

187
00:14:41.281 --> 00:14:42.617
And just kind of...

188
00:14:43.518 --> 00:14:46.521
You feel used. you know.

189
00:14:46.554 --> 00:14:50.958
you just want back
everything they took from you.

190
00:14:52.527 --> 00:14:54.161
I'm trying to track her down.

191
00:14:54.495 --> 00:14:55.929
I'll find her.

192
00:14:58.165 --> 00:14:59.333
Is that your husband?

193
00:15:00.134 --> 00:15:03.571
Oh. no.
That's. uh. my cousin Winthrop.

194
00:15:04.271 --> 00:15:05.239
Hmm.

195
00:15:07.174 --> 00:15:08.409
You need a hand?

196
00:15:08.442 --> 00:15:10.110
I've killed a few weeds
in my day.

197
00:15:10.144 --> 00:15:11.646
Honestly. No. you
don't need to.

198
00:15:11.679 --> 00:15:12.946
-You sure?
-Yeah. No. I--

199
00:15:12.980 --> 00:15:14.281
Your ice cream is
probably melted.

200
00:15:14.314 --> 00:15:15.382
No. That's fine.

201
00:15:15.416 --> 00:15:17.284
I can just put it
in your fridge.

202
00:15:18.352 --> 00:15:19.420
Um...

203
00:15:20.755 --> 00:15:22.289
-Oh. Ellen. Ellen.
-Ellen.

204
00:15:22.322 --> 00:15:23.591
Yeah. Uh.
Let me. uh...

205
00:15:23.625 --> 00:15:24.626
Okay. Here.

206
00:15:24.659 --> 00:15:25.426
You can get the other bag.

207
00:15:25.459 --> 00:15:27.662
I will.
I'm just going to show you

208
00:15:27.695 --> 00:15:29.496
where the kitchen
is first and then.

209
00:15:29.531 --> 00:15:30.464
Hi.

210
00:15:31.331 --> 00:15:32.332
Hi.

211
00:15:55.422 --> 00:15:58.058
Who watches TV on
such a beautiful day.

212
00:15:59.326 --> 00:16:00.662
It's a good day for gardening.

213
00:16:00.695 --> 00:16:01.663
Let's do it.

214
00:16:01.696 --> 00:16:03.163
Mm.

215
00:16:05.132 --> 00:16:08.368
It's so nice to have
somebody to actually talk to.

216
00:16:11.438 --> 00:16:12.607
Here are some gloves.

217
00:16:12.640 --> 00:16:14.308
How long ago did
your mother pass?

218
00:16:17.377 --> 00:16:18.713
I saw the photos.

219
00:16:21.583 --> 00:16:22.684
Just a few months back.

220
00:16:22.717 --> 00:16:23.718
Mm.

221
00:16:23.751 --> 00:16:25.118
She was pretty.

222
00:16:35.229 --> 00:16:36.230
Doesn't that hurt?

223
00:16:38.165 --> 00:16:39.399
Oh. Ellen...

224
00:16:42.135 --> 00:16:43.771
Everything hurts.

225
00:16:52.680 --> 00:16:53.548
Mm.

226
00:17:00.755 --> 00:17:02.256
Almost there?

227
00:17:02.289 --> 00:17:03.223
Mm.

228
00:17:14.101 --> 00:17:15.068
Sorry.

229
00:17:17.271 --> 00:17:18.506
Oh. It slipped.

230
00:17:20.742 --> 00:17:22.342
All right. here we go.

231
00:17:24.612 --> 00:17:27.147
Winthrop. dinner
if you're hungry.

232
00:17:34.187 --> 00:17:35.623
You must be Winthrop.

233
00:17:37.291 --> 00:17:39.527
Winthrop. Vahna.

234
00:17:39.561 --> 00:17:41.161
our neighbor who was
kind enough

235
00:17:41.194 --> 00:17:42.764
to provide us
with this beautiful food.

236
00:17:57.579 --> 00:18:01.315
So what's a guy like you
doing living with his cousin?

237
00:18:01.348 --> 00:18:03.585
Don't you have a job?

238
00:18:06.654 --> 00:18:08.188
He lined up a job
for the spring.

239
00:18:09.289 --> 00:18:10.658
Not too far away. actually.

240
00:18:10.692 --> 00:18:11.626
Oh. yeah.

241
00:18:12.760 --> 00:18:13.828
What kind of job?

242
00:18:17.497 --> 00:18:18.666
Sheet metal plant.

243
00:18:21.603 --> 00:18:23.103
Does he speak?

244
00:18:29.276 --> 00:18:30.545
I speak.

245
00:18:31.813 --> 00:18:34.515
Sorry. I was just teasing.
I didn't mean anything.

246
00:18:39.386 --> 00:18:42.289
Okay. Get home safely.

247
00:18:42.322 --> 00:18:43.591
Yeah.

248
00:18:43.625 --> 00:18:45.727
How long has Winthrop
been staying with you?

249
00:18:47.260 --> 00:18:48.261
Not long.

250
00:18:48.630 --> 00:18:50.598
Just be careful.

251
00:18:52.299 --> 00:18:55.335
I can tell that man has
done some terrible things.

252
00:19:00.374 --> 00:19:01.676
-Okay.
-Mm.

253
00:19:09.282 --> 00:19:10.283
Toodles.

254
00:19:28.636 --> 00:19:30.705
<i>I'm sorry. I didn't know</i>
<i>you were in there.</i>

255
00:19:31.405 --> 00:19:32.940
<i>It won't happen again.</i>

256
00:19:37.645 --> 00:19:41.214
You think you can hide from me?

257
00:19:43.250 --> 00:19:44.719
Anywhere you go...

258
00:19:44.752 --> 00:19:46.921
I will find you.

259
00:19:47.522 --> 00:19:49.857
Bitch! Bitch! Bitch!

260
00:19:49.891 --> 00:19:51.358
Bitch!

261
00:20:13.047 --> 00:20:14.448
Thank you.

262
00:20:16.584 --> 00:20:18.886
I wanted to apologize
again about last night.

263
00:20:20.454 --> 00:20:21.488
It's okay.

264
00:20:33.735 --> 00:20:34.969
The kitchen accident.

265
00:20:37.071 --> 00:20:38.405
In the mess hall.

266
00:20:40.575 --> 00:20:42.610
Had these huge vats of fry oil.

267
00:20:44.846 --> 00:20:47.715
Some guys were messing around.

268
00:20:48.716 --> 00:20:50.017
One of them tipped.

269
00:20:53.320 --> 00:20:54.488
Almost killed me.

270
00:20:54.756 --> 00:20:55.957
Probably should have.

271
00:21:08.970 --> 00:21:10.571
You fixed it.

272
00:21:10.605 --> 00:21:11.672
It's really beautiful.

273
00:21:23.350 --> 00:21:24.451
Thank you.

274
00:21:32.126 --> 00:21:34.729
We should have taken you in
when your parents died.

275
00:21:35.930 --> 00:21:37.397
I'm so sorry.

276
00:21:45.773 --> 00:21:46.874
Vahna.

277
00:21:46.908 --> 00:21:47.842
Hi.

278
00:21:49.010 --> 00:21:50.410
Hide the silverware.

279
00:21:51.879 --> 00:21:54.081
I heard about your
church fundraiser.

280
00:21:54.115 --> 00:21:55.616
so I brought this stuff.

281
00:21:55.650 --> 00:21:57.852
It's not a lot.
but I don't use it anymore.

282
00:21:57.885 --> 00:21:59.086
That's so generous.

283
00:21:59.120 --> 00:22:00.087
Yeah. And then I was...

284
00:22:00.121 --> 00:22:02.924
Well. I was just
sitting around bored sick

285
00:22:02.957 --> 00:22:06.561
and I thought maybe my new
friend Ellen wouldn't mind

286
00:22:06.594 --> 00:22:09.130
keeping her silly little
friend company for a while.

287
00:22:09.163 --> 00:22:11.364
Well. we're pretty
much done for the day.

288
00:22:11.398 --> 00:22:12.633
The sky's about to open up.

289
00:22:12.667 --> 00:22:14.669
Oh. well. look at that.
Yeah. okay.

290
00:22:25.513 --> 00:22:26.280
Good times.

291
00:22:26.314 --> 00:22:28.716
-Yeah.
-Good times and hard times.

292
00:22:30.718 --> 00:22:31.919
Oh. no.

293
00:22:33.020 --> 00:22:35.623
I know all about hard times.

294
00:22:35.656 --> 00:22:37.859
The cruelty people
are capable of.

295
00:22:38.693 --> 00:22:39.927
Like my father.

296
00:22:41.562 --> 00:22:43.598
He knew cruelty.

297
00:22:44.497 --> 00:22:46.534
He was an expert.

298
00:22:46.934 --> 00:22:50.605
Not only did he start to
sexually assault his daughter.

299
00:22:50.638 --> 00:22:52.840
when I was. like.
four years old.

300
00:22:53.608 --> 00:22:55.076
He thought it would be fun

301
00:22:55.109 --> 00:22:58.079
to pass her around to all
of his friends.

302
00:22:59.614 --> 00:23:02.016
All of them like
a cheap bottle of wine.

303
00:23:04.185 --> 00:23:05.786
Do you know what that's like?

304
00:23:06.587 --> 00:23:09.489
While your father sits back
and it's just like. you know.

305
00:23:09.523 --> 00:23:11.959
"Let it feel good.
Like. why are you crying?"

306
00:23:16.230 --> 00:23:17.430
No.

307
00:23:18.199 --> 00:23:19.399
I don't.

308
00:23:20.668 --> 00:23:21.969
And I see how strong you are.

309
00:23:23.204 --> 00:23:25.072
Survivors carry it
in their eyes.

310
00:23:27.141 --> 00:23:28.509
Strong.

311
00:23:28.776 --> 00:23:29.844
Yeah.

312
00:23:30.778 --> 00:23:31.879
No.

313
00:23:34.749 --> 00:23:38.886
I would die right now
if I had a choice.

314
00:23:41.488 --> 00:23:43.591
I just need a new fucking body.

315
00:23:47.895 --> 00:23:50.031
Every inch of this one hurts.

316
00:23:50.998 --> 00:23:54.502
I put the bird bath into
the shed so the paint won't run.

317
00:24:00.675 --> 00:24:02.643
I think I'm gonna rest
for a while.

318
00:24:02.677 --> 00:24:03.678
Tired?

319
00:24:04.812 --> 00:24:07.181
From all that yard work?

320
00:24:08.282 --> 00:24:10.117
Big. strong guy like you.

321
00:24:12.687 --> 00:24:14.188
What do you want from me?

322
00:24:16.057 --> 00:24:17.692
Everything.

323
00:24:18.893 --> 00:24:21.762
Ignore her. Winthrop.
She's being silly.

324
00:24:21.796 --> 00:24:23.798
Yes. ignore me.
I'm being silly.

325
00:24:30.071 --> 00:24:31.572
You can't trust him.

326
00:24:31.605 --> 00:24:33.207
Stop. You don't know him.

327
00:24:35.710 --> 00:24:37.812
He wants to fuck me
and probably you too.

328
00:24:39.146 --> 00:24:40.681
Probably you too.

329
00:24:40.715 --> 00:24:42.750
Don't be so naive.

330
00:24:42.783 --> 00:24:43.818
Can you dance with me?

331
00:24:43.851 --> 00:24:45.820
-I'm good. I'm good.
-Oh. please dance with me.

332
00:24:45.853 --> 00:24:46.887
-I won't bite.
-Really.

333
00:24:46.921 --> 00:24:48.522
I don't bite. I promise.

334
00:24:54.762 --> 00:24:58.933
You put up a very
puritan front. Ellen.

335
00:24:58.966 --> 00:25:02.903
But I think you got
some secrets in there.

336
00:25:03.738 --> 00:25:05.006
I don't have any secrets.

337
00:25:05.039 --> 00:25:05.973
No?

338
00:25:09.710 --> 00:25:10.778
It's getting late.

339
00:25:11.078 --> 00:25:12.847
I'm tired.
Let's get you home.

340
00:25:12.880 --> 00:25:15.082
I had to drink a lot of wine.
actually.

341
00:25:15.783 --> 00:25:18.219
A lot of wine.
and it's raining outside.

342
00:25:18.252 --> 00:25:21.222
And I don't want to crash
my bike into a ditch.

343
00:25:21.255 --> 00:25:22.890
Okay. Uh. I will drive you.

344
00:25:22.923 --> 00:25:24.158
We'll put your bike
in the back.

345
00:25:24.191 --> 00:25:25.993
I can't move.

346
00:25:26.027 --> 00:25:27.862
Come on. I'll help.
We can make it.

347
00:25:27.895 --> 00:25:30.264
I'll just sleep in
your bed tonight.

348
00:25:30.297 --> 00:25:32.066
It's fine.
You won't even notice I'm there

349
00:25:32.099 --> 00:25:33.701
because I'm a very
still sleeper.

350
00:25:33.734 --> 00:25:34.935
Like a rock. Look.

351
00:25:40.741 --> 00:25:41.842
Okay.

352
00:28:01.782 --> 00:28:03.484
I was wondering. if you might
like to join me

353
00:28:03.518 --> 00:28:04.752
for church this morning.

354
00:28:04.785 --> 00:28:05.853
It's a short service.

355
00:28:07.154 --> 00:28:08.255
That'd be okay.

356
00:28:08.289 --> 00:28:09.256
Oh. great.

357
00:28:10.424 --> 00:28:11.425
Morning.

358
00:28:12.326 --> 00:28:13.994
Good morning.

359
00:28:14.495 --> 00:28:18.232
I'm going to borrow this for a
couple days. if you don't mind.

360
00:28:18.265 --> 00:28:20.734
Actually. I was going to give
it to Winthrop for his room.

361
00:28:20.768 --> 00:28:22.002
Oh. he can manage.

362
00:28:22.036 --> 00:28:24.305
I just need to get my heat
turned back on.

363
00:28:25.039 --> 00:28:26.106
<i>Toodles!</i>

364
00:28:30.244 --> 00:28:31.245
Here we are.

365
00:28:39.019 --> 00:28:40.087
Good morning.

366
00:28:40.821 --> 00:28:42.056
That man?

367
00:28:42.089 --> 00:28:43.057
He scared me
to death last night.

368
00:28:43.090 --> 00:28:45.259
He showed up on my porch
at 2:00 in the morning.

369
00:28:45.527 --> 00:28:47.127
I had to get my husband's gun.

370
00:28:47.529 --> 00:28:49.096
I thought
he was going to break in.

371
00:28:49.129 --> 00:28:50.231
What are you talking about?

372
00:28:50.264 --> 00:28:51.432
You're okay.

373
00:28:51.465 --> 00:28:52.900
Everybody's okay.

374
00:28:53.267 --> 00:28:54.468
Let's go inside.

375
00:29:03.877 --> 00:29:05.746
Would it be okay if I stay
in the car?

376
00:29:07.147 --> 00:29:08.182
Of course.

377
00:29:15.222 --> 00:29:17.024
Hi Don.

378
00:29:18.593 --> 00:29:22.229
<i>...and Jacob said to Joseph.</i>
<i>go and see the world</i>

379
00:29:22.263 --> 00:29:23.998
<i>through thy neighbor's eyes.</i>

380
00:29:24.198 --> 00:29:27.034
<i>And the Bible tells us that</i>
<i>Lucifer mocked this.</i>

381
00:29:27.401 --> 00:29:29.803
<i>and he sent out his demons</i>
<i>to mock it</i>

382
00:29:29.837 --> 00:29:31.539
<i>and to weaken this idea</i>
<i>among men.</i>

383
00:29:32.172 --> 00:29:33.274
<i>Why?</i>

384
00:29:33.307 --> 00:29:34.875
<i>The Bible tells us this. too.</i>

385
00:29:34.908 --> 00:29:36.944
<i>Because it was more dangerous</i>
<i>to him</i>

386
00:29:36.977 --> 00:29:38.212
<i>than anything that--</i>

387
00:29:54.094 --> 00:29:55.195
Winthrop.

388
00:29:57.298 --> 00:30:00.100
You can't disappear
on people like that.

389
00:30:00.501 --> 00:30:01.503
I'm sorry.

390
00:30:05.973 --> 00:30:08.375
Were you at Denise
Minotka's last night?

391
00:30:08.409 --> 00:30:09.376
I don't remember.

392
00:30:10.545 --> 00:30:12.313
I didn't mean to scare anybody.

393
00:30:16.518 --> 00:30:18.586
Maybe it was sick or something.

394
00:30:19.987 --> 00:30:21.188
I tried to save it.

395
00:30:27.394 --> 00:30:29.330
You've always done this.
you know.

396
00:30:30.532 --> 00:30:32.199
You remember when you pulled

397
00:30:32.232 --> 00:30:35.069
that tiny. half dead
bird out of that dog's mouth.

398
00:30:36.937 --> 00:30:41.175
and you built a whole ICU
in a shoebox for it?

399
