Your smile when that
bird finally took flight.

400
00:32:03.023 --> 00:32:05.593
Winthrop. is that you?

401
00:32:23.611 --> 00:32:25.179
<i>Hello.</i>

402
00:32:27.549 --> 00:32:30.083
Come meet the Porta John Man.

403
00:32:33.454 --> 00:32:34.988
Porta John.

404
00:32:49.571 --> 00:32:50.572
Vahna.

405
00:32:56.477 --> 00:32:57.478
Vahna...

406
00:32:59.681 --> 00:33:01.215
Are you okay?

407
00:33:07.354 --> 00:33:08.523
Hold me.

408
00:33:12.560 --> 00:33:14.428
I know what he did to you.

409
00:33:14.461 --> 00:33:15.395
Who?

410
00:33:16.196 --> 00:33:17.699
Your uncle...

411
00:33:19.166 --> 00:33:21.703
keeping you in that cage.

412
00:33:24.104 --> 00:33:25.105
Now. now...

413
00:33:29.511 --> 00:33:31.813
Don't go losing your head.

414
00:33:31.846 --> 00:33:33.781
<i>John! John!</i>

415
00:33:42.289 --> 00:33:43.357
Who are you?

416
00:34:03.143 --> 00:34:04.579
I brought you some food.

417
00:34:06.480 --> 00:34:07.749
Feeling any better?

418
00:34:12.720 --> 00:34:15.455
It's been three days.
I'm going to call the doctor.

419
00:34:17.457 --> 00:34:19.092
God. it's cold in here.

420
00:34:25.900 --> 00:34:28.235
Tomorrow. I'm not
taking no for an answer.

421
00:34:28.570 --> 00:34:31.539
I'm going to drive up and
get that heater back from Vahna.

422
00:34:33.206 --> 00:34:34.609
Do you need anything
before I go?

423
00:35:12.346 --> 00:35:13.748
Vahna. it's Ellen.

424
00:35:41.843 --> 00:35:43.143
Hello?

425
00:36:30.658 --> 00:36:31.859
Ms. Hershbergen?

426
00:36:32.627 --> 00:36:34.361
I am Detective Tom Rausch.

427
00:36:37.431 --> 00:36:38.833
So you found her in there?

428
00:36:40.702 --> 00:36:42.469
Well. is there anyone
we can call

429
00:36:42.503 --> 00:36:43.705
someone to pick you up?

430
00:36:43.738 --> 00:36:45.372
Someone you can stay with
for a while?

431
00:36:45.405 --> 00:36:48.375
Oh. no. I'm okay.
I have someone staying with me.

432
00:36:48.408 --> 00:36:49.476
Thank you.

433
00:36:49.510 --> 00:36:50.912
Good. yeah.

434
00:36:51.311 --> 00:36:53.648
Well. I think you've had more
than enough for one night.

435
00:36:53.681 --> 00:36:55.683
so I'm gonna save my questions
for the morning. okay?

436
00:36:56.884 --> 00:36:58.285
- Thank you.
- All right.

437
00:37:16.838 --> 00:37:17.839
Oh.

438
00:37:18.573 --> 00:37:20.742
Vahna's... dead.

439
00:37:25.345 --> 00:37:26.379
She. uh...

440
00:37:28.683 --> 00:37:31.753
was beaten to death
it looked like.

441
00:37:33.353 --> 00:37:35.656
Why would anyone
want to do that?

442
00:37:38.726 --> 00:37:40.494
Since. unfortunately.

443
00:37:40.528 --> 00:37:42.730
you might be the last person
to see her alive

444
00:37:42.764 --> 00:37:44.464
and the one who found her body.

445
00:37:44.999 --> 00:37:47.769
would you mind if we take
a look around the house?

446
00:37:47.802 --> 00:37:48.569
Strictly routine.

447
00:37:48.603 --> 00:37:50.872
No. not at all.
Whatever you need.

448
00:37:51.672 --> 00:37:52.640
Now. you mentioned

449
00:37:52.673 --> 00:37:55.009
you went to Vahna Minter's house
for a heater.

450
00:37:55.843 --> 00:37:57.011
She borrowed mine.

451
00:37:57.044 --> 00:37:59.346
said she was going to bring
it back in a couple of days.

452
00:37:59.379 --> 00:38:00.948
but I hadn't heard from her
in over a week.

453
00:38:07.989 --> 00:38:09.322
And is this the heater?

454
00:38:10.390 --> 00:38:11.592
Uh yes. that's it?

455
00:38:15.563 --> 00:38:16.998
Is that a neighbor?
Who's that?

456
00:38:17.532 --> 00:38:20.034
That's my cousin. Winthrop.
He's staying with me.

457
00:38:20.067 --> 00:38:21.434
Does he know Vahna?

458
00:38:22.435 --> 00:38:24.539
She came over to the house
a couple of times.

459
00:38:24.572 --> 00:38:25.573
had dinner with us.

460
00:38:25.606 --> 00:38:26.774
Spent the night once.

461
00:38:27.542 --> 00:38:28.943
She slept over?

462
00:38:28.976 --> 00:38:32.513
It was raining and she didn't
feel well.

463
00:38:32.547 --> 00:38:33.748
so I offered
to drive her home. but...

464
00:38:38.418 --> 00:38:41.289
Okay. well. what's. uh.
Winthrop's full name.

465
00:38:43.691 --> 00:38:46.994
Oh. Winthrop Thomas Benson.

466
00:38:48.461 --> 00:38:51.532
And was he here with you last
Tuesday or Wednesday night?

467
00:38:52.600 --> 00:38:53.801
He's always here.

468
00:38:56.137 --> 00:38:57.337
Detective?

469
00:38:58.606 --> 00:38:59.707
Excuse me.

470
00:39:15.523 --> 00:39:17.825
My guys are going to finish up
here. but. um.

471
00:39:17.859 --> 00:39:19.927
would you mind bringing Winthrop
to the station

472
00:39:19.961 --> 00:39:21.461
first thing tomorrow morning?

473
00:39:21.494 --> 00:39:23.463
We'd like to ask him
a few questions as well.

474
00:39:24.699 --> 00:39:25.633
Sure.

475
00:39:25.833 --> 00:39:27.034
Have a good day. ma'am.

476
00:39:37.879 --> 00:39:38.980
Officer.

477
00:39:39.647 --> 00:39:40.848
Have a good day. sir.

478
00:39:40.882 --> 00:39:41.883
Thank you.

479
00:39:55.229 --> 00:39:56.364
Thanks for coming in.

480
00:39:56.396 --> 00:39:58.666
Oh. thank you for making
time for me. I appreciate it.

481
00:39:58.699 --> 00:39:59.800
-No problem.
-Thanks.

482
00:40:07.141 --> 00:40:08.509
Detective Rausch.

483
00:40:11.045 --> 00:40:12.680
Okay. Yeah.

484
00:40:15.216 --> 00:40:16.651
Yeah. yeah. yeah.

485
00:40:44.545 --> 00:40:46.781
I hear you like to take walks
late at night.

486
00:40:47.548 --> 00:40:51.484
Sometimes I can't sleep
and I get nightmares

487
00:40:51.519 --> 00:40:52.520
so I walk.

488
00:40:53.587 --> 00:40:56.489
The coroner says Vahna Minter
most likely died

489
00:40:56.524 --> 00:40:57.992
sometime Tuesday night.

490
00:40:58.025 --> 00:40:59.160
Were you out walking then?

491
00:40:59.193 --> 00:41:00.895
You see anything strange?

492
00:41:05.566 --> 00:41:06.968
So you have an OTH?

493
00:41:07.001 --> 00:41:10.671
<i>Records of several fights.</i>
<i>one with an officer.</i>

494
00:41:11.572 --> 00:41:12.773
And this one here.

495
00:41:13.874 --> 00:41:16.677
Looks like you nearly
beat this man to death.

496
00:41:16.711 --> 00:41:18.245
Lost vision in his right eye.

497
00:41:18.279 --> 00:41:19.213
Mhm. mhm. mhm.

498
00:41:20.848 --> 00:41:22.583
You want to talk to me about it?

499
00:41:30.825 --> 00:41:31.892
Listen. Winthrop

500
00:41:33.127 --> 00:41:34.195
I was in Kuwait.

501
00:41:35.763 --> 00:41:37.131
Two tours.

502
00:41:37.665 --> 00:41:40.267
I know the shit you see
when you close your eyes. okay?

503
00:41:40.301 --> 00:41:41.535
I've been there.

504
00:41:41.569 --> 00:41:43.004
But I'm gonna need you
to talk to me.

505
00:41:48.209 --> 00:41:51.278
All right.
You want to play hardball?

506
00:41:51.312 --> 00:41:52.813
Let's play hardball.

507
00:41:53.247 --> 00:41:54.949
I see you had
an accident at the base.

508
00:41:56.951 --> 00:41:58.719
You want to talk about that?

509
00:42:00.621 --> 00:42:01.722
Hm?

510
00:42:02.757 --> 00:42:05.192
Have you ever been
to Vahna Minter's house?

511
00:42:08.029 --> 00:42:10.097
