512
00:42:10.131 --> 00:42:11.198
Never with Ellen.

513
00:42:11.232 --> 00:42:12.867
Never one of your
midnight strolls.

514
00:42:12.900 --> 00:42:14.035
Never for something else.

515
00:42:14.068 --> 00:42:15.002
No!

516
00:42:22.810 --> 00:42:26.080
This mitt is one half of a pair.

517
00:42:26.113 --> 00:42:28.949
One of which was found in
Vahna Minter's kitchen.

518
00:42:28.983 --> 00:42:32.186
and the other of which
was found in your room.

519
00:42:34.255 --> 00:42:36.624
Now. I'd like for you
to tell me

520
00:42:36.657 --> 00:42:38.225
how this wound up
in your room.

521
00:42:39.160 --> 00:42:40.795
Excuse me.
Who are you?

522
00:42:41.829 --> 00:42:44.198
I'm Ellen Hershbergen.
That's my cousin.

523
00:42:44.231 --> 00:42:45.900
Oh. I see.

524
00:42:45.933 --> 00:42:47.334
Actually. I wouldn't mind
asking you

525
00:42:47.368 --> 00:42:48.869
a few questions
if you're willing

526
00:42:48.903 --> 00:42:50.171
to come down to the DA's office.

527
00:42:50.204 --> 00:42:51.138
Of course.

528
00:42:57.945 --> 00:43:00.147
Winthrop Benson.
we are placing you under arrest

529
00:43:00.181 --> 00:43:01.215
for the murder-
-What?!

530
00:43:01.248 --> 00:43:03.084
-of Vahna Minter.
-No.

531
00:43:03.117 --> 00:43:05.019
There is an explanation.
that mitt--

532
00:43:05.052 --> 00:43:07.822
Ms. Hershbergen you can explain
everything in the interview.

533
00:43:07.855 --> 00:43:10.291
For now. we are done here.
My office will be in touch.

534
00:43:10.324 --> 00:43:11.625
Let's go.

535
00:43:15.362 --> 00:43:17.098
I've been in law for 20 years.

536
00:43:17.131 --> 00:43:18.065
and I must say.

537
00:43:18.099 --> 00:43:19.934
I'm stunned they've
actually charged him.

538
00:43:19.967 --> 00:43:23.204
They have no DNA. no clear
prints. no motive.

539
00:43:24.071 --> 00:43:26.674
One troubling issue is this
ridiculous oven mitt

540
00:43:26.707 --> 00:43:28.042
they found in Winthrop's room.

541
00:43:28.075 --> 00:43:29.777
Yes. I wanted to talk to you
about that.

542
00:43:29.810 --> 00:43:31.345
So Vahna brought over
a bag of stuff

543
00:43:31.378 --> 00:43:33.013
for the church fundraiser.

544
00:43:33.047 --> 00:43:35.850
and the mitt was in there.
but there was only one.

545
00:43:35.883 --> 00:43:36.884
Oh. excellent.

546
00:43:36.917 --> 00:43:38.285
Winthrop must have found it

547
00:43:38.319 --> 00:43:40.287
and taken it into
his room for some reason.

548
00:43:41.956 --> 00:43:43.757
So what's the next step?

549
00:43:43.791 --> 00:43:44.925
Can I post bail?

550
00:43:44.959 --> 00:43:46.393
You may not need to.

551
00:43:46.427 --> 00:43:49.063
I've requested a preliminary
hearing to determine

552
00:43:49.096 --> 00:43:50.898
whether or not
they have enough evidence

553
00:43:50.931 --> 00:43:52.733
to even bring this case
to trial.

554
00:43:52.766 --> 00:43:55.136
Now. prosecution is certainly
going to make a big deal

555
00:43:55.169 --> 00:43:57.438
about Winthrop's
late night walks. but

556
00:43:57.471 --> 00:44:00.307
I found an expert who is
willing to submit an affidavit

557
00:44:01.008 --> 00:44:04.345
explaining the effects of PTSD
and how victims often have

558
00:44:04.378 --> 00:44:06.080
trouble sleeping.

559
00:44:06.113 --> 00:44:10.217
I know he has some issues.
but Winthrop is not a murderer.

560
00:44:11.018 --> 00:44:12.987
And from the moment I met Vahna.

561
00:44:13.020 --> 00:44:15.055
you could tell
something was very off.

562
00:44:15.089 --> 00:44:17.691
Oh. we have somebody looking
into her past as we speak.

563
00:44:19.126 --> 00:44:20.227
Good.

564
00:44:23.297 --> 00:44:24.298
All right.

565
00:44:25.332 --> 00:44:26.700
I appreciate your time.

566
00:44:26.734 --> 00:44:28.169
You're welcome.

567
00:44:31.238 --> 00:44:33.340
Porta John Man.

568
00:44:34.875 --> 00:44:36.410
Porta.

569
00:44:40.247 --> 00:44:41.315
No.

570
00:44:47.087 --> 00:44:49.089
Hey. hey!
Freak show.

571
00:45:34.301 --> 00:45:35.302
Hey!

572
00:45:52.820 --> 00:45:54.288
I don't feel right.

573
00:45:55.823 --> 00:45:56.824
Ellen...

574
00:45:57.458 --> 00:45:58.892
I'm seeing things.

575
00:46:00.394 --> 00:46:02.096
What kind of things?

576
00:46:02.129 --> 00:46:03.063
Just...

577
00:46:04.198 --> 00:46:05.366
flashes.

578
00:46:06.166 --> 00:46:09.236
But violent things.

579
00:46:10.538 --> 00:46:13.807
Like I'm seeing through
someone else's eyes.

580
00:46:14.475 --> 00:46:16.443
Thinking someone else's
thoughts.

581
00:46:20.615 --> 00:46:22.082
Winthrop.

582
00:46:24.285 --> 00:46:26.887
I need you to be
very honest with me.

583
00:46:28.523 --> 00:46:31.158
Did you have anything to do
with Vahna's murder?

584
00:46:33.427 --> 00:46:34.428
No.

585
00:46:36.096 --> 00:46:37.097
No.

586
00:46:37.931 --> 00:46:38.932
Okay.

587
00:46:39.534 --> 00:46:41.468
We're gonna get you
out of here.

588
00:46:41.502 --> 00:46:43.003
No.

589
00:46:46.073 --> 00:46:48.576
No. I don't mind being here.

590
00:46:50.311 --> 00:46:52.346
And I don't want you
to come back to visit.

591
00:46:54.181 --> 00:46:55.182
Guard!

592
00:46:56.483 --> 00:46:57.951
I'm finished in here.

593
00:47:08.929 --> 00:47:10.831
<i>I just knew the answers</i>
<i>lay with Vahna.</i>

594
00:47:11.332 --> 00:47:13.200
<i>But the woman was a phantom.</i>

595
00:47:13.434 --> 00:47:16.136
<i>I couldn't find her. anywhere.</i>

596
00:50:59.627 --> 00:51:01.763
<i>I'll let you sleep</i>
<i>for 10 hours</i>

597
00:51:01.796 --> 00:51:04.331
<i>and paint a rainbow on you.</i>

598
00:51:04.364 --> 00:51:07.100
<i>And then I'll slice you open</i>
<i>so your heart falls out</i>

599
00:51:07.134 --> 00:51:08.335
<i>before you wake up.</i>

600
00:51:08.803 --> 00:51:10.538
It's the first thing
that you will see

601
00:51:10.572 --> 00:51:13.340
me rubbing your heart blood
on my face.

602
00:51:14.308 --> 00:51:15.877
I'll be laughing at you

603
00:51:15.910 --> 00:51:18.412
as I feed
my little throat people.

604
00:51:18.445 --> 00:51:21.381
I'll use your blood
to wash my fucking dishes.

605
00:51:22.215 --> 00:51:23.718
Where did you get these?

606
00:51:23.751 --> 00:51:25.152
Vahna's house.

607
00:51:26.286 --> 00:51:27.855
I know. I just...

608
00:51:28.455 --> 00:51:30.558
You should have
seen him yesterday.

609
00:51:30.592 --> 00:51:33.360
He's terrified. and it just
feels like the police think

610
00:51:33.393 --> 00:51:34.629
they've got their man.

611
00:51:34.662 --> 00:51:38.800
Well. this falls right in line
with Vahna's very sordid past.

612
00:51:38.833 --> 00:51:39.767
What?

613
00:51:40.267 --> 00:51:41.268
I've searched.

614
00:51:41.301 --> 00:51:43.303
and I haven't found
anything online about her.

615
00:51:43.337 --> 00:51:44.672
It pays to have a good P.I.

616
00:51:45.372 --> 00:51:46.373
Here.

617
00:51:47.609 --> 00:51:49.777
He tracked a long line
of aliases.

618
00:51:49.811 --> 00:51:52.880
Vahna was constantly changing
names and appearances.

619
00:51:52.914 --> 00:51:53.848
Here.

620
00:51:56.316 --> 00:51:57.752
Inet Goodreaux.

621
00:51:58.620 --> 00:52:00.354
Zilka Goodhanz.

622
00:52:00.888 --> 00:52:02.456
Sarah Morrison.

623
00:52:03.357 --> 00:52:05.225
Francesca Milani.

624
00:52:05.960 --> 00:52:07.762
Noah Jules-Domley.

625
00:52:07.795 --> 00:52:10.497
Not to speak ill of
the dead. but she was insane.

626
00:52:11.633 --> 00:52:13.568
She was living
in Salt Lake City.

627
00:52:13.601 --> 00:52:15.570
Two young Mormon
boys came to her door

628
00:52:15.603 --> 00:52:17.337
and she invited them in...

629
00:52:17.371 --> 00:52:19.641
only to tie them up
in her basement for hours.

630
00:52:19.674 --> 00:52:22.844
forcing them to perform
various sex acts

631
00:52:22.877 --> 00:52:24.746
on her and each other.

632
00:52:24.779 --> 00:52:25.847
What?

633
00:52:25.880 --> 00:52:28.415
She was arrested. but by
the time of her arraignment.

634
00:52:28.448 --> 00:52:29.651
she had vanished.

635
00:52:29.684 --> 00:52:31.485
One year later.
you met her in Pontiac.

636
00:52:32.386 --> 00:52:34.421
The point is that she was
clearly not well.

637
00:52:34.454 --> 00:52:35.857
and there are
many people out there

638
00:52:35.890 --> 00:52:37.825
who might have
a vendetta against her.

639
00:52:37.859 --> 00:52:40.293
You bet your ass I'm going
to be spelling this out

640
00:52:40.327 --> 00:52:41.361
in my motion to dismiss.

641
00:52:41.395 --> 00:52:42.764
But I need you to promise me

642
00:52:42.797 --> 00:52:44.666
that you will
not go back to that house.

643
00:52:44.699 --> 00:52:46.668
Oh. you don't have to worry
about that.

644
00:52:48.502 --> 00:52:50.303
Just before we start.

645
00:52:50.337 --> 00:52:52.406
I know this would
be your first murder trial

646
00:52:52.439 --> 00:52:55.409
and a conviction could be
a big boost for your career.

647
00:52:55.442 --> 00:52:57.545
but it could also be
a big mistake.

648
00:52:57.979 --> 00:52:59.179
Hmm.

649
00:52:59.947 --> 00:53:01.049
Look. with all due respect--

650
00:53:01.082 --> 00:53:03.584
Did you know that Winthrop
was commended for bravery

651
00:53:03.618 --> 00:53:05.385
for saving a platoon
member's life?

652
00:53:05.419 --> 00:53:08.388
And that when he was caught
beating up that soldier.

653
00:53:08.422 --> 00:53:09.991
he was actually
defending himself?

654
00:53:10.024 --> 00:53:12.794
Did you know that the burn on
his leg was not an accident?

655
00:53:12.827 --> 00:53:16.296
It was revenge for testifying
against the soldier

656
00:53:16.329 --> 00:53:20.868
that attacked him and that
he was relentlessly abused

657
00:53:20.902 --> 00:53:25.238
because he's small. quiet
and a little delayed.

658
00:53:25.272 --> 00:53:28.509
But wouldn't you be delayed if
your parents died in a horrific

659
00:53:28.543 --> 00:53:32.580
car accident when you were only
10 and you were in that car.

660
00:53:32.613 --> 00:53:36.584
And now you are sent to live
with a sick and sadistic uncle

661
00:53:36.617 --> 00:53:38.586
who beats you repeatedly.

662
00:53:38.619 --> 00:53:41.321
And yet still. he's not violent.

663
00:53:41.354 --> 00:53:45.225
In fact. he is kind. empathetic.

664
00:53:47.028 --> 00:53:50.464
I have years of psychological
reports from the VA

665
00:53:50.497 --> 00:53:51.799
verifying all of this.

666
00:53:51.833 --> 00:53:53.868
So go ahead.

667
00:53:53.901 --> 00:53:55.603
Put your reputation on the line

668
00:53:55.636 --> 00:53:58.438
with nothing but
circumstantial evidence.

669
00:53:59.507 --> 00:54:00.508
Uh...

670
00:54:01.642 --> 00:54:02.877
I will sleep on it.

671
00:54:04.512 --> 00:54:07.314
I will see you in court tomorrow
as scheduled.

672
00:55:29.030 --> 00:55:31.866
Apparently the prosecution
has decided to delay

673
00:55:31.899 --> 00:55:35.002
the proceedings pending
more concrete evidence.

674
00:55:36.037 --> 00:55:37.572
I'll give you two weeks.

675
00:55:38.039 --> 00:55:39.472
So ordered.

676
00:55:52.053 --> 00:55:53.054
Are you okay?

677
00:55:54.155 --> 00:55:55.756
I thought you'd be ecstatic.

678
00:55:57.625 --> 00:55:58.626
I am.

679
00:56:00.061 --> 00:56:01.461
Okay.

680
00:56:02.563 --> 00:56:04.732
Call me if
you need anything.

681
00:56:20.748 --> 00:56:22.683
You may think you got away
with this.

682
00:56:22.717 --> 00:56:25.753
but you and I both know
the truth. don't we. Winthrop?

683
00:56:54.916 --> 00:56:56.651
I told you we'd get you home.

684
00:57:04.025 --> 00:57:05.126
How are the headaches?

685
00:57:09.730 --> 00:57:10.731
Well...

686
00:57:11.899 --> 00:57:13.466
I'm going to head to bed and...

687
00:57:14.635 --> 00:57:16.003
we can talk in the morning

688
00:57:16.037 --> 00:57:18.072
once we both had a good
night's sleep. okay?

689
00:57:20.608 --> 00:57:22.576
Can I sleep with you tonight?

690
00:57:30.818 --> 00:57:32.787
Your room's all ready for you.

691
00:57:32.820 --> 00:57:34.221
Clean sheets and all.

692
00:57:35.289 --> 00:57:36.791
You'll be good.

693
00:59:08.282 --> 00:59:10.284
-Yeah.
-Hey. it's Nina.

694
00:59:10.317 --> 00:59:13.054
I know it's late.
but guess what?

695
00:59:13.087 --> 00:59:14.855
We found Winthrop.

696
00:59:14.889 --> 00:59:16.791
He's at a homeless shelter.

697
00:59:16.824 --> 00:59:18.626
I'll send you the address.

698
00:59:18.659 --> 00:59:19.727
Thank you. Nina.

699
00:59:25.199 --> 00:59:27.001
Sh-sh-sh.

700
00:59:27.334 --> 00:59:28.803
Here you go.

701
00:59:35.276 --> 00:59:36.710
Hello. Winthrop.

702
00:59:41.816 --> 00:59:43.117
It's good to see you.

703
00:59:59.767 --> 01:00:00.835
Okay.

704
01:00:02.136 --> 01:00:04.238
Listen. I want to take
you home. okay?

705
01:00:10.911 --> 01:00:14.782
All right. well. at least
let me give you some money

706
01:00:15.983 --> 01:00:19.687
so you can get a real meal
and some rest. okay?

707
01:00:24.291 --> 01:00:26.961
Where does Grace Beck live?

708
01:00:27.461 --> 01:00:29.263
I-I-I don't know who that is.

709
01:00:32.133 --> 01:00:34.101
I don't know her.
I don't know who she is.

710
01:00:44.245 --> 01:00:46.213
Okay. Okay. Okay.

711
01:00:46.247 --> 01:00:48.782
You- you have to give me
something to go on.

712
01:00:48.816 --> 01:00:49.750
Who is she?

713
01:00:55.990 --> 01:00:57.725
She's your teacher?

714
01:01:00.394 --> 01:01:05.933
Where does Grace Beck live?

715
01:01:05.966 --> 01:01:07.067
All right.

716
01:01:07.501 --> 01:01:09.336
All right. I'm gonna
try to find out.

717
01:01:10.104 --> 01:01:11.305
Grace Beck.

718
01:01:12.773 --> 01:01:13.807
Okay.

719
01:01:15.743 --> 01:01:17.711
Come back home
whenever you're ready.

720
01:01:27.788 --> 01:01:31.992
Bitch. bitch. bitch. bitch.

721
01:01:32.026 --> 01:01:35.196
Bitch. bitch. bitch.

722
01:01:39.033 --> 01:01:42.336
Bitch. bitch. bitch. bitch!

723
01:01:42.369 --> 01:01:44.205
Bitch. bitch. bitch. bitch!

724
01:01:53.214 --> 01:01:54.848
<i>Nina was right.</i>

725
01:01:54.882 --> 01:01:57.251
<i>It does pay to know</i>
<i>a good investigator.</i>

726
01:02:00.321 --> 01:02:02.223
<i>We had found Grace Beck.</i>

727
01:02:15.035 --> 01:02:16.036
Um...

728
01:02:17.037 --> 01:02:18.138
Hello.

729
01:02:18.172 --> 01:02:19.541
<i>Hi. Miss Hershbergen.</i>

730
01:02:19.574 --> 01:02:21.375
<i>My name</i>
<i>is Robert Edgewood.</i>

731
01:02:21.408 --> 01:02:24.745
<i>I'm a rep with the state</i>
<i>looking for Winthrop Benson.</i>

732
01:02:25.879 --> 01:02:26.981
Hi.

733
01:02:27.014 --> 01:02:27.781
Hi.

734
01:02:27.815 --> 01:02:30.552
I'm with the state
welfare office.

735
01:02:30.585 --> 01:02:33.053
There's some money owed
to Mr. Benson.

736
01:02:33.087 --> 01:02:35.322
and we have this as his
last known address.

737
01:02:35.356 --> 01:02:36.924
Is he home?

738
01:02:36.957 --> 01:02:40.094
Uh. unfortunately. he's
not living here right now.

739
01:02:40.494 --> 01:02:41.929
You might be able to find him

740
01:02:41.962 --> 01:02:44.566
at the shelter
on Stanton up in Buffalo.

741
01:02:44.599 --> 01:02:46.033
Oh. okay.

742
01:02:46.066 --> 01:02:48.902
Um. well. if you do hear
from him.

743
01:02:48.936 --> 01:02:51.071
I'd really appreciate you
giving us a call.

744
01:02:51.105 --> 01:02:52.139
Of course.

745
01:02:52.172 --> 01:02:53.207
Thank you.

746
01:02:53.240 --> 01:02:54.275
Have a good day.

747
01:02:54.308 --> 01:02:55.242
Yeah. you too.

748
01:03:42.956 --> 01:03:45.492
I'm sorry we haven't seen
Winthrop in over a week now.

749
01:03:45.993 --> 01:03:47.895
I thought maybe he had
gone back home with you.

750
01:03:49.129 --> 01:03:50.497
Thank you.

751
01:03:52.333 --> 01:03:56.103
Um. you might want to try down
at the Covington overpass.

752
01:03:56.503 --> 01:03:59.607
It's a long shot. but some
people set up tents under there.

753
01:04:00.274 --> 01:04:01.275
Much appreciated.

754
01:05:06.674 --> 01:05:08.610
Please stay back.

755
01:05:09.009 --> 01:05:10.010
Please.

756
01:05:12.312 --> 01:05:15.517
Did you find Grace Beck?

757
01:05:17.050 --> 01:05:18.152
Yes.

758
01:05:18.185 --> 01:05:19.521
You have to tell me why--

759
01:05:19.554 --> 01:05:21.054
Stay back I said!

760
01:05:26.026 --> 01:05:27.629
Tell me where she is. bitch.

761
01:05:29.096 --> 01:05:30.197
or I'll kill you too!

762
01:05:34.001 --> 01:05:36.937
You did not kill Vahna.

763
01:05:43.110 --> 01:05:44.044
Vahna.

764
01:05:44.077 --> 01:05:46.980
I know this isn't you
and I will help you.

765
01:05:47.014 --> 01:05:48.550
Grace can help me!

766
01:05:50.484 --> 01:05:51.686
Bring her here.

767
01:06:14.642 --> 01:06:16.410
Hello. this is Grace Beck.

768
01:06:16.443 --> 01:06:17.679
Ellen Hershbergen.

769
01:06:17.712 --> 01:06:19.179
I reached out about
Vahna Minter.

770
01:06:19.213 --> 01:06:21.048
Yes. Ellen.

771
01:06:21.081 --> 01:06:22.015
I'm sorry.

772
01:06:22.049 --> 01:06:24.084
It's just getting word
that accused killer

773
01:06:24.117 --> 01:06:25.620
is out there looking for me.

774
01:06:25.653 --> 01:06:28.088
Brought back all the Vahna stuff
I've been trying to forget.

775
01:06:29.323 --> 01:06:30.457
I hate to admit it. but...

776
01:06:31.659 --> 01:06:33.093
I'm glad Vahna is dead.

777
01:06:34.461 --> 01:06:38.198
Anything you're willing
to tell me is invaluable.

778
01:06:43.203 --> 01:06:44.438
Vahna was a...

779
01:06:45.372 --> 01:06:48.342
student in my poetry class.

780
01:06:49.511 --> 01:06:52.145
I was going through
some dark times.

781
01:06:52.179 --> 01:06:55.650
Vahna played on that
vulnerability like a maestro.

782
01:06:57.852 --> 01:07:01.789
It got very intense.
very quick and...

783
01:07:03.290 --> 01:07:04.358
there were drugs and...

784
01:07:07.094 --> 01:07:08.161
Domination.

785
01:07:08.195 --> 01:07:13.233
I realized that she was
obsessed with what I let her

786
01:07:14.334 --> 01:07:15.670
do to me.

787
01:07:16.169 --> 01:07:19.306
She liked to hang me.

788
01:07:19.841 --> 01:07:21.408
It was sick.

789
01:07:21.441 --> 01:07:24.478
I wanted out.
and she became furious.

790
01:07:24.812 --> 01:07:25.680
She...

791
01:07:27.214 --> 01:07:29.551
said that I would
never be free of her.

792
01:07:30.618 --> 01:07:34.388
And that's when she told me
about the Porta John Man.

793
01:07:36.456 --> 01:07:40.828
This man told Vahna she no
longer had to be afraid

794
01:07:40.862 --> 01:07:42.664
that she would now live forever.

795
01:07:42.697 --> 01:07:44.699
[sinister voice
I got something for you.

796
01:07:45.332 --> 01:07:46.768
And you get to keep it.

797
01:07:52.239 --> 01:07:55.577
And Vahna swore to me
that if I ever left her.

798
01:07:55.610 --> 01:07:58.445
she would do whatever it took
to find me.

799
01:08:01.148 --> 01:08:04.184
I'm. um. changing my number. so.

800
01:08:04.217 --> 01:08:06.420
Wait...
I found some letters.

801
01:08:07.220 --> 01:08:09.122
Some are to you.

802
01:08:09.591 --> 01:08:11.325
I just thought if we could meet.

803
01:08:11.358 --> 01:08:12.292
You saw the letters.

804
01:08:12.326 --> 01:08:13.861
maybe we could make
some sense of this.

805
01:08:16.163 --> 01:08:17.297
Grace.

806
01:08:20.868 --> 01:08:22.102
Grace...

807
01:08:23.771 --> 01:08:25.740
Vahna's not dead.

808
01:08:25.773 --> 01:08:27.542
What do you mean?

809
01:08:27.575 --> 01:08:28.509
Move.

810
01:08:28.776 --> 01:08:30.477
And leave no trace.

811
01:08:31.211 --> 01:08:33.313
Vahna is not dead.

812
01:09:17.257 --> 01:09:18.258
Help!

813
01:09:18.492 --> 01:09:19.794
Help!

814
01:09:25.800 --> 01:09:28.235
Where's Grace Beck?!

815
01:09:28.803 --> 01:09:31.471
Where is Grace Beck?!

816
01:09:35.308 --> 01:09:36.410
Kevin.

817
01:09:38.780 --> 01:09:40.515
What the fuck is going on?

818
01:09:40.548 --> 01:09:41.582
Drop it!

819
01:09:42.717 --> 01:09:43.951
- Drop it!

820
01:09:46.020 --> 01:09:47.522
Who are you?

821
01:09:47.722 --> 01:09:48.923
Got him.

822
01:09:54.327 --> 01:09:55.663
Let's get him outta here.

823
01:09:55.997 --> 01:09:57.397
Did he hurt you?

824
01:09:57.632 --> 01:09:58.465
James.

825
01:10:08.609 --> 01:10:09.610
Hey!

826
01:12:14.001 --> 01:12:16.503
What are you doing
with Winthrop?

827
01:12:16.537 --> 01:12:17.872
It's freezing out here.

828
01:12:17.905 --> 01:12:19.841
Come inside where we can talk.

829
01:12:22.677 --> 01:12:26.047
My name is James.
and this is Kevin.

830
01:12:30.618 --> 01:12:31.919
We'll be inside.

831
01:12:57.211 --> 01:13:00.480
Hi. my name is James Light

832
01:13:00.514 --> 01:13:03.483
and I'm a priest
like Father Caldwell.

833
01:13:05.920 --> 01:13:08.089
And this is Doctor Emily Warren.

834
01:13:08.122 --> 01:13:09.590
Hello. Ellen.

835
01:13:09.624 --> 01:13:10.758
How's Winthrop doing?

836
01:13:10.791 --> 01:13:11.926
Sleeping peacefully.

837
01:13:11.959 --> 01:13:13.194
I'd like to see him.

838
01:13:13.227 --> 01:13:15.763
It will take some time for the
tranquilizers to wear off.

839
01:13:15.796 --> 01:13:17.932
but I can assure you
he's safe.

840
01:13:17.965 --> 01:13:19.834
Here. why don't you have
a seat

841
01:13:19.867 --> 01:13:20.968
and we'll tell you everything.

842
01:13:29.944 --> 01:13:35.783
We're dealing with nothing less
than evil incarnate.

843
01:13:35.816 --> 01:13:38.019
Some people call them demons.

844
01:13:38.986 --> 01:13:42.590
Imps. Succubi. Djinni.

845
01:13:42.623 --> 01:13:46.093
They like to nestle in and hide.

846
01:13:46.928 --> 01:13:49.530
forcing us to seek them out.

847
01:13:49.563 --> 01:13:53.534
One of these entities
had been in Vahna Minter

848
01:13:53.567 --> 01:13:55.435
for a very long time.

849
01:13:56.570 --> 01:14:00.141
and is now residing in Winthrop.

850
01:14:02.009 --> 01:14:04.845
Vahna was taken very young.

851
01:14:05.513 --> 01:14:10.785
The evil infusing in her
its own twisted desires.

852
01:14:11.185 --> 01:14:13.754
becoming obsessed
with Grace Beck.

853
01:14:14.155 --> 01:14:17.858
But Grace had enough
self-worth to get away in time.

854
01:14:17.892 --> 01:14:20.528
And this is when
we lost track of Vahna.

855
01:14:20.561 --> 01:14:21.529
Which is too bad

856
01:14:21.562 --> 01:14:24.098
because I believe
we could have captured it

857
01:14:24.131 --> 01:14:25.533
and saved her life.

858
01:14:26.100 --> 01:14:27.201
How?

859
01:14:27.234 --> 01:14:31.072
Evil is seeking those
who've been weakened by abuse.

860
01:14:31.105 --> 01:14:35.176
neglect. drugs like
Vahna Minter or Winthrop.

861
01:14:35.209 --> 01:14:39.080
The abuse rewires pathways.
making the brain

862
01:14:39.113 --> 01:14:42.016
more vulnerable. allowing
possession to take hold.

863
01:14:42.049 --> 01:14:48.255
But in very rare cases. a brain
is forming a neural cage

864
01:14:48.289 --> 01:14:50.191
that an entity cannot escape.

865
01:14:51.092 --> 01:14:52.593
You lost me here.

866
01:14:52.960 --> 01:14:54.862
We have such a brain.

867
01:14:55.129 --> 01:14:56.630
Kevin. do you mind?

868
01:15:02.570 --> 01:15:04.839
The book tells us about them.

869
01:15:06.140 --> 01:15:10.044
Now. the language used
is very archaic.

870
01:15:10.077 --> 01:15:13.781
but it translates
something akin to lockbox.

871
01:15:15.282 --> 01:15:19.086
Now. the only way to save
Winthrop now is

872
01:15:19.120 --> 01:15:22.289
to have the very
powerful force inside him

873
01:15:22.323 --> 01:15:26.994
moved into another host.
one that he can't escape.

874
01:15:27.028 --> 01:15:28.029
A lockbox.

875
01:15:28.062 --> 01:15:31.966
Surely you sense something
strange in Winthrop.

876
01:15:32.266 --> 01:15:33.834
A change.

877
01:15:34.368 --> 01:15:35.569
Yes.

878
01:15:36.170 --> 01:15:37.938
He told me he felt like

879
01:15:37.972 --> 01:15:40.074
he was thinking someone
else's thoughts.

880
01:15:44.712 --> 01:15:45.980
Here it comes.

881
01:15:59.226 --> 01:16:00.861
What are you doing
with that boy?

882
01:16:00.895 --> 01:16:02.730
James. we need
to get him upstairs.

883
01:16:03.397 --> 01:16:08.135
That boy was in a coma at
Saint Mary's for almost a year.

884
01:16:08.335 --> 01:16:12.373
His brain scan shows
he has the neural cage.

885
01:16:12.406 --> 01:16:13.674
What?

886
01:16:13.707 --> 01:16:14.975
So he was sent to us.

887
01:16:15.943 --> 01:16:17.945
and he just might save Winthrop.

888
01:16:17.978 --> 01:16:19.847
Are you fucking kidding me?

889
01:16:19.880 --> 01:16:21.215
He's the lock box?

890
01:16:21.715 --> 01:16:23.918
He's more than a child.

891
01:16:23.951 --> 01:16:28.989
He has the ability to absorb
pain like water into sand.

892
01:16:29.256 --> 01:16:32.760
The boy was born to parents
whose cruelty

893
01:16:32.793 --> 01:16:34.929
was matched only
by their neglect.

894
01:16:35.696 --> 01:16:37.798
They drugged him.

895
01:16:37.832 --> 01:16:39.233
They abandoned him.

896
01:16:39.266 --> 01:16:42.136
So now we do our best
to take care of him.

897
01:16:42.703 --> 01:16:44.772
But he was built for this.

898
01:17:16.871 --> 01:17:19.106
Yeah. Brave boy.

899
01:17:19.140 --> 01:17:20.074
Mm.

900
01:17:20.908 --> 01:17:23.344
We should be good
to go by sunset.

901
01:17:44.498 --> 01:17:46.400
Do you have a nosebleed?

902
01:17:46.433 --> 01:17:47.368
Mmhmm.

903
01:17:47.902 --> 01:17:48.736
Here.

904
01:17:50.871 --> 01:17:51.872
I got it.

905
01:18:07.188 --> 01:18:09.256
Feed us now.

906
01:18:12.359 --> 01:18:14.028
Why are you here?

907
01:18:15.863 --> 01:18:17.231
You vile...

908
01:18:17.264 --> 01:18:19.266
obscene creatures.

909
01:18:21.202 --> 01:18:22.870
We are you.

910
01:18:25.306 --> 01:18:26.941
And if you let them do this.

911
01:18:26.974 --> 01:18:28.976
Winthrop will die.

912
01:18:49.564 --> 01:18:50.764
James.

913
01:18:52.534 --> 01:18:55.970
Those things in that boy

914
01:18:57.539 --> 01:19:01.075
just told me that if you
do this. Winthrop will die.

915
01:19:01.108 --> 01:19:03.043
They spoke to you?

916
01:19:03.077 --> 01:19:04.011
Yeah.

917
01:19:05.846 --> 01:19:08.115
They are the prince of lies.

918
01:19:08.148 --> 01:19:10.251
He does not stand in the truth

919
01:19:10.284 --> 01:19:13.053
because there
is no truth in him.

920
01:19:13.087 --> 01:19:14.421
So no one has ever died.

921
01:19:16.890 --> 01:19:20.794
There is always a chance
that something goes wrong.

922
01:19:22.597 --> 01:19:24.098
How many have you lost?

923
01:19:26.934 --> 01:19:28.035
Two.

924
01:19:28.068 --> 01:19:29.236
Out of how many?

925
01:19:30.871 --> 01:19:31.872
Eight.

926
01:19:34.441 --> 01:19:37.044
The evil that is in Winthrop.

927
01:19:37.077 --> 01:19:39.980
do you know how many
lives it has destroyed?

928
01:19:40.014 --> 01:19:41.583
Condemning their souls to hell.

929
01:19:41.616 --> 01:19:42.850
So this is a bargain?

930
01:19:42.883 --> 01:19:43.917
No.

931
01:19:43.951 --> 01:19:45.319
It is God's work.

932
01:19:45.352 --> 01:19:48.289
God doesn't trade souls.
That is the devil's work.

933
01:19:48.322 --> 01:19:51.925
Morgan Hetfield.
a mother of five.

934
01:19:51.959 --> 01:19:53.427
Brandon Paige. a surgeon

935
01:19:53.460 --> 01:19:55.429
who has since saved
hundreds of lives.

936
01:19:55.462 --> 01:19:57.464
These are just two
of the people

937
01:19:57.498 --> 01:19:59.500
this remarkable boy
has saved.

938
01:20:03.337 --> 01:20:04.338
All right.

939
01:20:05.205 --> 01:20:06.473
I'll tell you what.

940
01:20:07.509 --> 01:20:10.177
If you believe what we're doing
is wrong.

941
01:20:10.210 --> 01:20:12.913
then take Winthrop
and walk out that door.

942
01:20:12.946 --> 01:20:14.148
We won't stop you.

943
01:20:19.353 --> 01:20:22.289
Winthrop is not dying tonight.

944
01:20:22.990 --> 01:20:24.425
Do you understand that?

945
01:21:08.102 --> 01:21:09.303
Now. now.

946
01:21:13.675 --> 01:21:16.210
Don't go losing your head.

947
01:21:22.416 --> 01:21:23.417
Who are you?

948
01:21:27.689 --> 01:21:29.923
That's who I am.

949
01:21:29.957 --> 01:21:31.559
Not to sound like your uncle.

950
01:21:32.092 --> 01:21:34.328
I'm not done with you.

951
01:21:40.033 --> 01:21:41.101
Argh!

952
01:21:48.308 --> 01:21:50.612
I've got something for you.

953
01:21:52.580 --> 01:21:54.148
And you.

954
01:21:54.415 --> 01:21:55.550
Get.

955
01:21:56.316 --> 01:21:57.985
To keep it.

956
01:24:29.269 --> 01:24:31.573
Sorry. We should have
known better. I'm sorry.

957
01:24:32.306 --> 01:24:33.841
All right.
We'll take him down now.

958
01:24:33.875 --> 01:24:36.310
All right. let's get you up.
Winthrop.

959
01:24:36.711 --> 01:24:37.645
Okay.

960
01:24:45.920 --> 01:24:47.789
Let's take him
to the basement.

961
01:25:31.833 --> 01:25:33.735
What do we do now?

962
01:25:34.368 --> 01:25:35.670
We wait.

963
01:26:14.709 --> 01:26:15.810
Is that normal?

964
01:26:16.410 --> 01:26:17.679
It's fine.

965
01:26:20.782 --> 01:26:22.349
Help me!

966
01:26:25.787 --> 01:26:26.888
Help!

967
01:26:34.494 --> 01:26:35.596
What?

968
01:26:37.330 --> 01:26:38.533
What just happened?

969
01:26:40.735 --> 01:26:42.269
What's going on?

970
01:26:42.302 --> 01:26:43.470
The video always cuts out.

971
01:26:43.503 --> 01:26:45.873
We're not allowed to see what
happens in the transition.

972
01:26:45.907 --> 01:26:47.307
Ellen!

973
01:26:49.844 --> 01:26:51.612
Ellen! Help!

974
01:26:53.648 --> 01:26:54.716
- Help

975
01:26:56.818 --> 01:26:57.985
What?

976
01:26:59.921 --> 01:27:00.922
James?

977
01:27:15.469 --> 01:27:16.938
James. We're losing him.

978
01:27:26.614 --> 01:27:27.749
Ellen?

979
01:27:27.782 --> 01:27:28.783
Ellen!

980
01:27:56.343 --> 01:27:57.344
Oh.

981
01:27:57.645 --> 01:27:59.279
No!

982
01:28:02.016 --> 01:28:03.785
No!

983
01:28:15.530 --> 01:28:16.564
Ugh!

984
01:30:05.039 --> 01:30:06.040
Mom.

985
01:30:27.828 --> 01:30:28.863
My...

986
01:30:29.897 --> 01:30:30.898
Ellen.

987
01:30:31.699 --> 01:30:33.067
You're not her.

988
01:30:33.968 --> 01:30:35.970
Don't you dare use her voice.

989
01:30:38.706 --> 01:30:40.041
I'm Winthrop.

990
01:30:41.609 --> 01:30:44.545
You knew where he was going.

991
01:30:45.579 --> 01:30:49.784
To that sick sadistic uncle

992
01:30:49.817 --> 01:30:54.622
who would beat him
until he could no longer cry.

993
01:30:54.655 --> 01:30:55.589
No.

994
01:30:57.224 --> 01:30:58.960
I didn't know.

995
01:30:58.993 --> 01:31:00.628
Don't lie to me again.

996
01:31:03.664 --> 01:31:05.232
You did know.

997
01:31:07.068 --> 01:31:08.069
Yes.

998
01:31:12.707 --> 01:31:14.108
I know who I owe.

999
01:31:17.912 --> 01:31:19.180
And you're not him.

1000
01:31:40.768 --> 01:31:41.769
Hello.

1001
01:31:47.341 --> 01:31:48.542
Hi.

1002
01:31:49.176 --> 01:31:50.244
I've got to go.

1003
01:31:54.682 --> 01:31:55.816
Do you have a name?

1004
01:31:56.317 --> 01:31:59.653
I used to. but I don't remember.

1005
01:32:02.723 --> 01:32:04.525
Thank you for saving Winthrop.

1006
01:32:13.300 --> 01:32:15.036
You can walk?

1007
01:32:16.871 --> 01:32:18.172
Yes.

1008
01:32:53.107 --> 01:32:54.575
Ellen?

1009
01:33:00.347 --> 01:33:01.348
Where is it?

1010
01:33:02.716 --> 01:33:04.919
No more games.

1011
01:33:12.159 --> 01:33:14.328
Open the door!!!

1012
01:33:17.398 --> 01:33:18.599
Ellen.

1013
01:33:20.901 --> 01:33:23.037
You interrupted us.
I don't have it.

1014
01:33:23.070 --> 01:33:25.039
Ellen! We're coming in!

1015
01:33:26.006 --> 01:33:27.708
Open the door!

1016
01:33:27.741 --> 01:33:28.843
I can still finish this.

1017
01:33:28.876 --> 01:33:29.877
He's lying.

1018
01:33:29.910 --> 01:33:30.945
Open the door!

1019
01:33:30.978 --> 01:33:31.912
Ellen!

1020
01:33:47.394 --> 01:33:48.462
God.

1021
01:33:49.463 --> 01:33:53.367
give me counsel. for I am
facing the Prince of Lies.

1022
01:33:53.400 --> 01:33:57.438
Give me the wisdom to not fall
for his wicked tricks.

1023
01:33:57.471 --> 01:34:00.774
for it is but deception
that gives him his power.

1024
01:34:00.808 --> 01:34:02.676
It is the Prince of Lies.

1025
01:34:02.710 --> 01:34:04.778
God. give me counsel.

1026
01:34:05.412 --> 01:34:07.248
...For facing the Prince
of Lies.

1027
01:34:09.450 --> 01:34:10.918
What is it. then?

1028
01:34:12.153 --> 01:34:13.154
What's the lie?

1029
01:34:19.860 --> 01:34:21.128
It's in me.

1030
01:34:25.933 --> 01:34:26.934
Ellen!

1031
01:34:30.871 --> 01:34:32.139
Touch my hand!

1032
01:34:32.173 --> 01:34:36.944
You will not touch the boy!

1033
01:35:41.576 --> 01:35:44.078
He's got it.
It's um...

1034
01:35:44.111 --> 01:35:45.112
Okay.

1035
01:35:45.513 --> 01:35:46.514
Okay.

1036
01:36:07.535 --> 01:36:09.136
What happened down there?

1037
01:36:11.905 --> 01:36:13.240
It tried to pull me apart.

1038
01:36:15.909 --> 01:36:16.944
Didn't work.

1039
01:36:20.014 --> 01:36:21.348
Someone brought you up. right?

1040
01:36:24.285 --> 01:36:25.286
Yeah.

1041
01:36:27.121 --> 01:36:28.822
The boy is resting now.

1042
01:36:29.156 --> 01:36:30.558
-I'll pay him a visit.
-Okay.

1043
01:36:32.594 --> 01:36:36.130
If we give you a tape recorder
would you be willing

1044
01:36:36.163 --> 01:36:40.367
to share what happened on record
just for us

1045
01:36:40.401 --> 01:36:42.169
for the next time we
try to save someone?

1046
01:36:43.504 --> 01:36:44.505
Sure.

1047
01:36:45.172 --> 01:36:46.173
Okay.

1048
01:36:48.142 --> 01:36:49.243
Thank you. James.

1049
01:36:50.044 --> 01:36:51.345
Oh. yes.

1050
01:36:52.112 --> 01:36:53.380
You're welcome.

1051
01:37:22.409 --> 01:37:26.180
That thing was destroying
the last good memory I had.

1052
01:37:29.283 --> 01:37:31.051
But you wouldn't let it.

1053
01:37:39.226 --> 01:37:40.894
Thank you.

1054
01:37:43.964 --> 01:37:45.633
Let's not make a thing of it.

1055
01:38:12.393 --> 01:38:14.228
<i>Dear cousin Ellen.</i>

1056
01:38:14.261 --> 01:38:16.430
<i>I saw this Michael</i>
<i>the Archangel</i>

1057
01:38:16.463 --> 01:38:19.466
<i>vanquishing the demon. and</i>
<i>it reminded me of you.</i>

1058
01:38:21.201 --> 01:38:23.571
<i>I wanted to let you know</i>
<i>I started my new job</i>

1059
01:38:23.605 --> 01:38:25.472
<i>and I really like it so far.</i>

1060
01:38:26.173 --> 01:38:27.575
